{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50fcd3a7-e621-4a86-9fc2-89836cf8f451","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages** — In your test `.csproj`, replace:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep `xunit` 2.9.3 as-is — it's compatible.\n\n**2. Enable the platform** — Add this property to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly (it's now an executable):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --list-tests\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n```\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Your test project now produces an **executable** (not just a DLL).\n- CLI options use `--` prefix (e.g., `--filter`, `--list-tests`).\n- `.runsettings` files still work but some VSTest-specific settings may not apply.\n- If you use `xunit.runner.json`, it continues to work normally.\n\nThat's the core migration — no test code changes needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11360ee8-a122-45a8-85a2-cdd65a28952d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":418,"requestId":"2863:101CE8:168BD5F:17EE174:6A045FC9"},"id":"03924114-6290-4a9d-8be8-4f61975d7858","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:14.528Z","parentId":"835b47e1-2217-47a2-8799-12ab5b6b668c"}
